						<p><hi rend="bold">[Hoyasaḷa] Viśvanāthadēva: Year 3, Siṅga (Āvaṇi)-ba. 11, Saturday, Punarpūśam = 1299 A.D., August 22.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is built in the middle. It records that from the year quoted the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉa</hi> villages belonging to the temple of Brahmīśvaramuḍaiyanāyiṉār were made <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> (rent-free).</p>						

